TITLE: Accessing Zustand Store Outside Components
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to access and manipulate Zustand store state outside of React components.
SOURCE: https://github.com/pmndrs/zustand/blob/main/README.md#2025-04-22_snippet_7

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
const useDogStore = create(() => ({ paw: true, snout: true, fur: true }))

// Getting non-reactive fresh state
const paw = useDogStore.getState().paw
// Listening to all changes, fires synchronously on every change
const unsub1 = useDogStore.subscribe(console.log)
// Updating state, will trigger listeners
useDogStore.setState({ paw: false })
// Unsubscribe listeners
unsub1()

// You can of course use the hook as you always would
function Component() {
  const paw = useDogStore((state) => state.paw)
  ...
```

