TITLE: Calculating Winner in Tic-Tac-Toe Game with JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: Function that determines if there is a winner in a Tic-Tac-Toe game by checking all possible winning combinations of three squares in a row, column, or diagonal. Returns the winning player ('X' or 'O') or null if there is no winner.
SOURCE: https://github.com/pmndrs/zustand/blob/main/docs/guides/tutorial-tic-tac-toe.md#2025-04-22_snippet_22

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
function calculateWinner(squares) {
  const lines = [
    [0, 1, 2],
    [3, 4, 5],
    [6, 7, 8],
    [0, 3, 6],
    [1, 4, 7],
    [2, 5, 8],
    [0, 4, 8],
    [2, 4, 6],
  ]

  for (let i = 0; i < lines.length; i++) {
    const [a, b, c] = lines[i]
    if (squares[a] && squares[a] === squares[b] && squares[a] === squares[c]) {
      return squares[a]
    }
  }

  return null
}
```

